title: The Junior Classics - Volume 8: Animal and Nature Stories
author: Selected and arranged by William Patten
snippet: And the whole summer passed by, and another summer after that, andstill more summers. The Beeches went on growing, and at last quiteovertopped the Little Oak.

title: The Junior Classics - Volume 8: Animal and Nature Stories
author: Selected and arranged by William Patten
snippet: The Beeches only laughed and went on growing. At last they closedtogether over the Little Oak's head, and then he died.

title: The Junior Classics - Volume 8: Animal and Nature Stories
author: Selected and arranged by William Patten
snippet: The Beeches laughed with their little, tiny green leaves, but saidnothing.
